{
  "texts": [
    "For example, Wang et al. (2022) use these visualizations to show a machine room or container with (near) real-time data overlaid for temperature, pressure, and other IoT data.",
    "The general complexity and size of ports is certainly the reason why different forms of 3D visualization can be found in almost all use cases of the digital twin discussed in the analyzed literature.",
    "In addition, the visualizations can serve as a method for interpreting the results of simulations performed with other systems.",
    "VR systems are just another use of this type of visualization, although potentially even more intuitive for the user.",
    "The benefits resulting from an implementation will be especially high in the areas of maintenance and training (Sanchez-Gonzalez et al. 2022)."
  ]
}